          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "TRN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Neutron TOF Spectrometer had the following",
                "parameters: fast chopper with diameter 300 mm, flight",
                "path - 69.74 m, energy resolution 1.0 mcs/m, 0.22 mcs/m",
                "and  0.055 mcs/m."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Metal powder of tungsten, enriched with W-180 up to",
                "95.1%, was used to prepare two samples for transmission",
                "measurements. Parameters of tungsten-180 samples:",
                "1)weight 2.547g, dimension 2.06x14.87x13.19 mm3;",
                "2)weight 4.338g, dimension 2.06x15.0x23.5 mm3.",
                "Content of other W isotopes in sample was 4.8% for 182W",
                "and 0,1% for 184W. The repacked  sample (4.338g) was",
                "irradiated in the reactor neutron fluence 4*10e20 n/cm2",
                "to get the radioactive W-181."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SLA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Analysis and calculations for neutron resonances",
                "were  fulfilled using shape method in accordance with",
                "singlelevel Breit-Wigner formalism."
              ]
            }
          ],
